name: Grand Valley State University - John C Kennedy Hall of Engineering
directions: If you go in the door facing Front St, just go straight through the open area until you're in a hallway, it'll be on your left. There is an entrance/exit along the path that connects the outside area to Fulton, which is directly next to the restroom too - if you need to go straight in without encountering people there's a high success rate for that. Easily the best neutral downtown bathroom for introverts
comment: There is a desk but if you walk with purpose they won't question it. Closed during typical college breaks, open for summer classes for parts of the summer.

name: Grand Valley State University - Cook Devos Center for Health Sciences
directions: First floor, if you go in the main doors it's past the lobby almost to the area with the coffee place. That area is one long hallway and the bathroom is kind of close to a side door in the bank of glass windows facing the street
